The paper deals with image colorization, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The focus is on manga, which is a form of graphic art, and the paper proposes a method to improve the quality of colorization in this specific context. Therefore, it is likely to be relevant to the graphics subfield (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the use of segmentation, which is a common technique in multimedia processing (cs.MM). The proposed method is based on conditional GANs, which is a popular deep learning approach (cs.LG). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of limited training data, which is a common challenge in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
